{"body": "So if I understand correctly, the current PR will likely break a large volume of applications out there that use the current loose hexadecimal formatting for Postgres. If that is correct, is there a way that we could add a server warning when the buggy formatting is used? This could be an interim step, where we state that the formatting option being used is being phased out, and then put this current fix into the release we name in the warning.\r\n\r\nAdmittedly this is a lot of additional work and organization. But issue #7619 seems rather significant.\r\n\r\nThoughts?", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/14920502", "created_at": "2013-03-14T18:30:42Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/8206#issuecomment-14920502", "updated_at": "2013-03-14T18:30:42Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 8206, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/geopet/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/geopet/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/geopet/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/geopet", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/geopet/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/geopet", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/geopet/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/71e5c7e9a86b98fc12a880450762d9d5?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fc437b36ac74d2e33ae8f39388b47f3a3.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/geopet/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/geopet/received_events", "gravatar_id": "71e5c7e9a86b98fc12a880450762d9d5", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/geopet/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "geopet", "type": "User", "id": 632827, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/geopet/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237f521bd3543c15100ab68"}, "id": 14920502, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/8206"}
